com.swfm.mica
Class MiBounds

java.lang.Object
  com.swfm.mica.MiBounds
All Implemented Interfaces:
MiiTypes
public class MiBounds
extends java.lang.Object
implements MiiTypes

This class represents a rectangular area and is heavily used by Mica, typically whereever the dimensions of an area is needed.

The bounds of this class can be in an uninitilized state (reversed) in which case xmin < xmax and ymin < ymax. This can be tested for by calling the method #isReversed.

For very time or memory sensitive applications, there is a explicitly-accessed allocation pool to prevent the inevitable overhead of allocating and deallocating many instances of MiBounds (see #newBounds).

Version:

Author:
